<doc id="1101837" wikidata="Q168953" url="?curid=1101837" title="Aïn Defla Province">
<text>Aïn Defla (, is a wilaya (&quot;province&quot;) in northern Algeria. It is located to the southwest of Algiers, the capital. Localities in Ain Delfa include Aïn Defla, Miliana, El Attaf, Djelida and Djendel.

==History==
The province was created from Chlef Province in 1984.

==Administrative divisions==
It is made up of 14 districts and 36 municipalities.

The districts are:

