<doc id="1102024" wikidata="Q1327323" url="?curid=1102024" title="Kōchō">
<text>was a after &quot;Bun&#x27;ō&quot; and before &quot;Bun&#x27;ei.&quot; This period spanned the years from February 1261 to February 1264. The reigning emperor was .

==Change of era==
* ; 1261: The new era name was created to mark an event or a number of events. The previous era ended and a new one commenced in &quot;Bun&#x27;ō&quot; 2. The era name comes from &quot;The Political Program of the Zhenguan Period&quot; and combines the characters (&quot;broad&quot;) and (&quot;long&quot;).

==Events of the &quot; Kōchō&quot; era==
* June 11, 1261 (&quot;Kōchō 1, 12th day of the 5th month&quot;): Nichiren was exiled to Itō in the Izu Province.
* March 19, 1262 (&quot;Kōchō 2, 28th day of the 11th month&quot;): Shinran passes away at the age of 90
* April 1, 1263 (&quot;Kōchō 3, 22nd day of the 2nd month&quot;): Nichiren was pardoned.

