<doc id="1102057" wikidata="Q1194244" url="?curid=1102057" title="Shōgen">
<text>was a after &quot;Shōka&quot; and before &quot;Bun&#x27;ō.&quot; This period spanned the years from March 1259 through April 1260. The reigning emperors were and .

==Change of era==
* 1259 : The new era name was created to mark an event or a number of events. The years of the Shōgen era were part of a period marked by famine and epidemics; and the era name was changed in quick succession in the hope that this might bring the period to a close. The previous era ended and a new one commenced in &quot;Shōka&quot; 3.

==Events==
* 1259 (&quot;Shōgen 1, 11th month&quot;): In the 14th year of Go-Fukakusa&quot;-tennō&quot;″s reign (後深草天皇14年), the emperor abdicated; and the succession (&quot;senso&quot;) was received by his younger brother. Shortly thereafter, Emperor Kameyama is said to have acceded to the throne (&quot;sokui&quot;).

